<div id="c32">
<p>@Fin: &#8220;I don‚Äôt program outside of work, apart from the odd script or php debug.&#8221;  Honestly, that alone is a problem. Good programmers write code; the ones who only do it at work are just doing it because it&#8217;s a job.</p>

<p>Code written for work is often written under conditions guaranteeing it&#8217;s compromised in some way and probably isn&#8217;t representative of the best work you&#8217;re capable of.  The code you write for yourself is going to be your best stuff.</p>

<p>On another topic, I&#8217;m bothered by the fact that this process is slanted in favor of social extroverts. You&#8217;re probably missing good people who just don&#8217;t do well in the kind of situation you&#8217;re creating, which many people find more stressful than a formal interview.</p>

