<p class="posted">posted by John Corbin
 on November 29, 2009 <a href="#c33" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>
<div id="c34">
<p>You have to be a little careful of this approach with regards to anti-discrimination laws.  When you don&#8217;t have any sort of firm metrics by which to judge candidates, it&#8217;s easy for someone to say they didn&#8217;t get the job because you don&#8217;t get along with black/white/latino/asian people.</p>

<p class="posted">posted by Sam
 on November 29, 2009 <a href="#c34" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
