<div id="c68">
<p>@Joe:</p>

<p>In a large company it doesn&#8217;t have to be just HR involved in hiring.</p>

<p>I worked for a reasonably large firm (offices in 10 countries) with a pretty big IT department.  For IT hires the interview process included someone from HR but also the line manager and the team leader of the team they would be working in.  Sometimes senior developers would be involved as well.  The HR person was only there to cover the bureaucratic stuff.  The line manager and team lead were there for the technical stuff, and to see if the prospective hire would fit in.  Worked well.</p>

